<DOC><DOCNO> AP880812-0296 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-12-88 2253EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-UnionPacific     08-12 0191</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Union Pacific,0199</SECOND><HEAD>Union Pacific Assumes Control Of Missouri-Kansas-Texas Railroad</HEAD><DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Union Pacific Railroad assumed control Fridayof the Missouri-Kansas-Texas Railroad, railroad officials announced.   In a news release, Union Pacific said the takeover had beenapproved May 18 by the Interstate Commerce Commission.   Union Pacific reached agreement with Katy Industries in 1986 toacquire its railroad, more commonly known as the Katy, forapproximately $110 million and assume its $250 million debt.   Operational changes on the Katy will be phased in to assure asmooth transition, Union Pacific said.   Union Pacific said the changes will be made as labor agreementsare reached outlining employee transfers and other details. Onemove will be the installation of Union Pacific's TransportationControl System on Katy routes, bringing Union Pacific'scomputerized customer service program to Katy shippers.   The Katy is a 3,100-mile regional railroad connecting theMidwest with the Texas Gulf Coast. Union Pacific and Katy have hadseveral joint operating arrangements to use of each other's tracks.   Union Pacific serves the West Coast, Texas Gulf Coast and suchmajor trade cities as Chicago, St. Louis, Memphis, Tenn.; and NewOrleans.</TEXT></DOC>